Overview
Jardinains Game is a 2D arcade-style brick breaker game developed using Java as part of my MCA minor project.
The game demonstrates core Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts, GUI development, and event handling using AWT/Swing.
The objective of the game is to control the paddle to bounce the ball and break all the bricks to complete the level.

Technologies Used
 Java
 OOP Concepts
 AWT / Swing
 Event Handling
 Java Graphics

Features
 Interactive paddle and ball mechanics
 Collision detection system
 Score tracking system
 Game Over and Restart functionality
 Multiple bricks layout
 Keyboard controls

How to Play
 Use Left Arrow (←) to move paddle left
 Use Right Arrow (→) to move paddle right
 Break all bricks to win the game
 If the ball touches the bottom, the game is over

